.SH "NAME"
gshadow \- shadowed crew file
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP

/etc/gshadow
gotz nuff tha shadowed shiznit fo' crew accounts\&.
.PP
This file must not be readable by regular playas if password securitizzle is ta be maintained\&.
.PP
Each line of dis file gotz nuff tha followin colon\-separated fields:
.PP
\fBgroup name\fR
.RS 4
It must be a valid crew name, which exist on tha system\&.
.RE
.PP
\fBencrypted password\fR
.RS 4
Refer to
\fBcrypt\fR(3)
for details on how tha fuck dis strang is interpreted\&.
.sp
If tha password field gotz nuff some strang dat aint a valid result of
\fBcrypt\fR(3), fo' instizzle ! or *, playas aint gonna be able ta bust a unix password ta access tha crew (but crew thugz do not need tha password)\&.
.sp
Da password is used when a user whoz ass aint a gangmember of tha crew wants ta bust tha permissionz of dis crew (see
\fBnewgrp\fR(1))\&.
.sp
This field may be empty, up in which case only tha crew thugz can bust tha crew permissions\&.
.sp
A password field which starts wit a exclamation mark means dat tha password is locked\&. Da remainin charactas on tha line represent tha password field before tha password was locked\&.
.sp
This password supersedes any password specified in
/etc/group\&.
.RE
.PP
\fBadministrators\fR
.RS 4
It must be a cold-ass lil comma\-separated list of user names\&.
.sp
Administrators can chizzle tha password or tha thugz of tha group\&.
.sp
Administrators also have tha same permissions as tha thugz (see below)\&.
.RE
.PP
\fBmembers\fR
.RS 4
It must be a cold-ass lil comma\-separated list of user names\&.
.sp
Members can access tha crew without bein prompted fo' a password\&.
.sp
Yo ass should use tha same list of playas as in
/etc/group\&.
.RE
.SH "FILES"
.PP
